# Supabase Conventions

## Client Selection

| Context | Client to use |
|---------|--------------|
| Browser / React component | `createBrowserClient` from `@/lib/supabase` |
| Server Component / Route Handler | `createServerClient` (cookies) from `@/lib/supabase` |
| GitHub Actions / backend job | `service_role` key via env only тАФ never in `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` |

## Auth

Always get the current user with `getUser()`, never `getSession()` for authorization:

```ts
// тЬЕ server-side auth check
const { data: { user }, error } = await supabase.auth.getUser();
if (!user) redirect('/login');

// тЭМ getSession() is unauthenticated тАФ JWT only, not verified server-side
```

## Row-Level Security

All tables use RLS. Include `user_id` on inserts for user-owned tables that carry an owner column.

```ts
// тЬЕ insert with owner
await supabase.from('tblPortfolio').insert({ ...data, user_id: user.id });

// тЭМ missing user_id тАФ RLS WITH CHECK will reject it
await supabase.from('tblPortfolio').insert({ ...data });
```

User-owned tables: `tblPortfolio`, `tblPortfolioPositions`, `tblPositionExits`, `watchlists`, `watchlist_tickers`, `user_preferences`.
`tblPositionExits` does not carry `user_id` directly; its RLS policies resolve ownership through `tblPortfolioPositions` тЖТ `tblPortfolio`.
Reference/market data tables (`sectors`, `earnings_calendar`, `income_statements`) are public-read, service_role-write.

## Never Expose

- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` тАФ server/CI only
- Any key in `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` other than the publishable anon key

## `raw_user_meta_data` is not safe for authorization

Store authorization data in `app_metadata` only.
